This paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) subfield of Computer Science, specifically in the area of dialog research. The paper discusses strategies for mapping dialog act annotations of the LEGO corpus into the communicative functions of the ISO 24617-2 standard, which is a common task in NLP. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms and techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the analysis of data, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
